org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.internal.files

Class MediaTransferProtocolMonitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.internal.files.MediaTransferProtocolMonitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Closeable, java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public class MediaTransferProtocolMonitor
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Closeable
    MediaTransferProtocolMonitor helps keep MTP views on desktops in sync with the contents of the actual file system on the phone. We introduce some latency to the scanning so as to minimize overhead.

      • noteFile

        public void noteFile(java.io.File file)
        A public file has been updated or created. Inform the MediaScanner of this fact so that it will show up in Media Transfer Protocol UIs on connected desktop computers. This is necessary due to a very-long-standing bug in Android.
        Parameters:
        file - the file or directory that is to be noted
        See Also:
        Android bug
